name: float_f64_largest_subnormal
description: |
  This is the largest binary64 subnormal, immediately below the smallest
  positive normal. The adjacent pair crosses the encoding boundary where the
  implicit leading significand bit appears, exposing normalization, conversion,
  rounding, and off-by-one errors near gradual underflow.
format: hex
decode-as: f64
pair:
  - with: smallest-positive-normal.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f64"
  - "subnormal"
  - "underflow"
  - "boundary"
---
ff ff ff ff ff ff 0f 00   # 0x000fffffffffffff: largest subnormal
